modules.description: Generates a prime number of a specified order using modular arithmetic. Operates on large integers represented as Z.t from the Zarith library. Used to establish cryptographic parameters in finite field constructions.

Provides a function to retrieve a specific constant value from the Fp module. Operates on the Fp.t data type, which represents elements of a finite field. Used to access precomputed values necessary for cryptographic operations.

Provides operations for arithmetic in finite fields, including addition, multiplication, inversion, and random element generation. Works with elements represented as arbitrary-precision integers within a field of prime order. Used to create JavaScript-compatible finite field implementations for cryptographic or mathematical applications.

Generates prime numbers using modular arithmetic and handles finite field elements for cryptographic applications. Supports operations on Z.t for large integers and Fp.t for field elements, enabling secure parameter generation and constant retrieval. Allows construction of cryptographic primitives by combining prime generation with field element manipulation. Can be used to create secure finite fields or access precomputed constants for encryption protocols.
